faa-rma pack — content licence
===============================

This pack is derived from:
    System Reliability, Maintainability, and Availability (RMA) Handbook
    FAA-HDBK-006D (8 October 2020), superseding FAA RMA-HDBK-006C V1.1 (15 November 2015)
    Federal Aviation Administration, NAS System Engineering & Integration Office

Source licence: Public Domain (US Government work)  (tier 1 — see ../../docs/SOURCE-VETTING.md)
No source-material download link is published (see ../../docs/LICENSING.md).

This handbook is a work of the United States Government, prepared by the Federal Aviation
Administration, and is therefore NOT subject to copyright protection in the United States
(17 U.S.C. 105). It is in the public domain: anyone may reproduce, transform, and
redistribute it for any purpose, including commercially, without permission. Attribution to
the FAA is provided as a courtesy (see the repository NOTICE), not a legal obligation. The
FAA does not endorse this pack or its authors.

GUIDANCE-ONLY CAVEAT (stated on the handbook's own title page): the handbook declares
"This handbook is for guidance only. Do not cite this document as a requirement." This pack
is a synthesized, transformed set of reference notes built from that guidance — it is not an
authority to cite in a contract, specification, or requirement, and the same caveat carries
forward to anything generated from it.

THIRD-PARTY MATERIAL CAVEAT: the handbook references — but this pack does NOT reproduce — a
number of external standards that remain the copyright of their publishers, including the DoD
MIL-STD/MIL-HDBK series (721C, 882E, 1629A, 3034A, 217F, 189C), NASA SP-2016-6105 and
NASA-STD-8729.1A, NUREG/CR-6101, IEEE Std 1633-2016, RTCA DO-178C and DO-278A, and SAE
JA1011. This pack contains only synthesized, original-wording notes that NAME those documents
and describe how the FAA handbook uses them; none of their text is reproduced here.

